rXiv Audio & Speech", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.24596v1/2603.24596v1/opd_fig2.png", "score": 15}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2603.24680v1", "title": "ReDiPrune: Relevance-Diversity Pre-Projection Token Pruning for Efficient Multimodal LLMs", "summary": "Abstract: Recent multimodal large language models are computationally expensive because Transformers must process a large number of visual tokens. We present \\textbf{ReDiPrune}, a training-free token pruning method applied before the vision-language projector, where visual features remain rich and d...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.24680", "source": "arXiv CV", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.24680v1/2603.24680v1/sec/figures/arxiv_figure.png", "score": 12}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2603.24653v1", "title": "From Weights to Concepts: Data-Free Interpretability of CLIP via Singular Vector Decomposition", "summary": "Abstract: As vision-language models are deployed at scale, understanding their internal mechanisms becomes increasingly critical. Existing interpretability methods predominantly rely on activations, making them dataset-dependent, vulnerable to data bias, and often restricted to coarse head-level exp...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.24653", "source": "arXiv CV", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.24653v1/2603.24653v1/x1.png", "score": 11}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2603.24810v1", "title": "Unified Diffusion Refinement for Multi-Channel Speech Enhancement and Separation", "summary": "Abstract: We propose Uni-ArrayDPS, a novel diffusion-based refinement framework for unified multi-channel speech enhancement and separation. Existing methods for multi-channel speech enhancement/separation are mostly discriminative and are highly effective at producing high-SNR outputs. However, the...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.24810", "source": "arXiv Audio & Speech", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.24810v1/2603.24810v1/x1.png", "score": 10}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2603.23625v1", "title": "Evaluating a Multi-Agent Voice-Enabled Smart Speaker for Care Homes: A Safety-Focused Framework", "summary": "Abstract: Artificial intelligence (AI) is increasingly being explored in health and social care to reduce administrative workload and allow staff to spend more time on patient care. This paper evaluates a voice-enabled Care Home Smart Speaker designed to support everyday activities in residential ca...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.23625", "source": "arXiv AI", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.23625v1/2603.23625v1/Figures/Final_Fig_RAGv2.png", "score": 9}]}